reviewText: Fantastic story about real life events and situations. A MUST see film!!!

Excellent work by Kyle T. Miller. I thoroughly enjoyed the plot and more importantly the characters were believable. Newcomer Niya Davis is a force to be reckoned with. I will be looking for more from this director and from all of the actors!
A fantastic movie that demonstrates human frailty and how love remains even after years of separation. This movie has lots of twists and turns and keeps you on the edge of your seat.
finally a movie that made sense. it's worth watching.
Well organized movie. Simple and realistic. Good movie for a young couple just starting out on a date. Happy ending.
I like watching independent movies. It was good and I would watch it again.
Very good, kept me and my husband engaged on a cold Saturday evening.
Great story line, great music, and great actors. Definitely a must see!
think most of the 4/5 starts are fake- this a Z-list movie- bad acting - stupid script
Words cannot describe how good this movie is!
Ok

Sorry, I struggled through to complete this movie, however I wasn't impressed. This is the first review I've written that strongly urges others they can watch it, but in my opinion the acting was pretty poor, most predicaments some got into were so obvious and predictable. Some of the actors were sobbing but they've were no tears. Whoever wrote the screenplay, made a nice attempt to write about a womanizer, but the actor protraying the part needs to continue to learn his craft. This movie for me fell short ........kind of disappointing.
It was ok.

I absolutely Love this movie,,,,My husband and I watched it twice!. I recommend this for anyone who wants a good plot that will make you laugh and cry.  Great job with the writing , music and directing.
It was ok.  A straight forward, simple  plot.
Great movie! A love story.
Awesome movie

I think the movie is a great inspiration to love in this real life we live in.  You never know what could happen. It's a low budget film but well worth watching.  You go through so many emotions and you are left guessing the outcome.  Hats off to Kyle Miller and crew, actors and to the plot of the story.  I will be watching for more
Really out standing meaning loved it.

By no means was it the greatest movie ever done but I didn't expect that. What I did want was a story where the actors wanted to be a part of the story, completely and not merely reciting words in front of a camera I wanted them to feel inspired by what they were doing and the message they were looking to express was truly conveyed. This movie told a story very common in society today, and one that I can truly relate to. Love indeed does conquer all and no matter what, when God says its right its right.

I personally loved the movie. I felt inspired and immediately called friends to tell them to watch it. So many good points, so many moments that sparked emotions. Thank you all for putting this movie together. THANK YOU

My hat off to you all
I like the fact that it kept you guessing,When you thought it was over or coming to a end something else Happened, very enjoyable!
very good

I loved the play Ashley & Jeremy, on which the movie is based. knowing how movies made from books or plays don't always get the small nuisances across on the big screen, I didn't have high expectations, but I loved every minute of it. This is only the beginning from new director Kyle Miller.
Good acting. But too long, too predictable, too common of a story. Upsetting moments no tears.
How love takes all... Great over all .... Must see
It was a'ight. Most of the acting was mediocre. The story was predictable. Too long.
This movie was a refreshing change.  I appreciated the story line as well as the acting.  I would like to see more movies like t his.
It was an okay movie, it was really long.
Started off not liking this movie only to stick with and ending up loving it. Relatable love story with religious overtones that are subtle but true.  Great cast with a non predictable storyline.
Great

I loved the movie. I loved how the prophetic was introduced in this movie. Not many movies offer scenes with the prophetic in the script. The story plot was great, the love triangle was very much so like relationships today. The redemption was awesome. Me and my wife enjoyed it very much.
Did not like it
It kept my attention.
